== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled @water{} into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Plant-Based Mince ==

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) or use a #garlic press{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Once hot, add the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} to the pan.

Use a #spoon{} to mash into a mince-like texture as it cooks. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

== Chilli Sauce ==

Add the garlic and @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} to the plant-based mince. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and @water{150%milliliters} into the pan. Add a @?sugar{pinch}. Stir together and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

== Tomato Salsa ==

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomatoes{2}(cut into 1cm chunks).

Pop the tomato chunks into a #small bowl{} with the @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

> Optional: you can add other salsa ingredients if desired.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together, then set your salsa aside.

== Assembly ==

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chilli, tomato salsa and grated Cheddar in separate sections over the rice, then add a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams}.

Finish with a sprinkle of @?chilli flakes{1%pinch} for those who'd like some more heat (add less if you'd prefer things milder).

> Enjoy!